{"key":"processedPost-8665892","value":{"id":8665892,"first":8660854,"last":8665892,"when":1216705286,"utime":"07/22/08 08:41 AM","content":"That humidifier needs to be on a timer.&nbsp; Tweak the timer so you maintain 95% humidity.&nbsp; It should need to run no more than 25% of the time to achieve that.<br />Also, move the humidifier back from the wall.&nbsp; The output is at about an 80 degree angle upwards, so the direct stream is hitting your plastic sheeting, causing water droplets to form there.<br />There is no such thing as too high of humidity.&nbsp; You can also place several trays of perlite on the floor to catch drips.<br />RR","title":"Re: Condensation In Greenhouse"}}